> Also what is going on when the 3rd gear keeps
> slipping?<<

First of all, make sure your clutch cable is adjusted
properly. If it is "slipping" in third gear, then
crawl under the bus and turn the wingnut on the end of
the clutch cable OUT (counterclockwise) a few turns
and see if that helps your slippage...

